contentrichtext.text: {{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}} '''Picket Lake''' is an [[unorganized territory]] located in [[St. Louis County, Minnesota|St. Louis County]], [[Minnesota]], [[United States]]. As of the [[United States Census, 2000|2000 census]], its population was zero. ==Geography== According to the [[United States Census Bureau]], the unorganized territory has a total area of 37.0 square miles (95.8 km²); 35.2 square miles (91.1 km²) of it is land and 1.8 square miles (4.7 km²) of it is [[water]]. The total area is 4.87% water. {{St. Louis County, Minnesota}} {{coord|48|06|22|N|92|23|06|W|display=title}} [[Category:Populated places in St. Louis County, Minnesota]] [[Category:Unorganized territories in Minnesota]]
